        <abstract>
            <t>This draft describes the Decimal Time Protocol (DTP), specifies its formal structure and summarizes information useful for its implementation. DTP provides a system in which time is measured and represented using a base-10 numbering system for various time units, such as days, hours, minutes, and seconds. Decimal time systems aim to simplify time calculations and provide a consistent, uniform structure for measuring time.</t>
        </abstract>
